  "text": "Our TweeTIME system consists of two major components as shown in Figure 3 proposed by [CITATION_1] . Each event consists of one or more named entities, in addition to the date on which the event takes place, for example [Mercury, 5/9/2016] . Tweets are first processed by a Twitter named entity recognizer [CITATION_2] , and a generic date resolver [CITATION_3] . Events are then extracted based on the strength of association between each named entity and calendar date, as measured by a G 2 test on their co-occurrence counts. More details of the Event Extractor can be found in Section 5.1. The following two sections describe the details of our Temporal Recognizer and Temporal Normalizer separately.",
